    <p> I have already seen most of the countries centrally and west of Europe and I can only say Ireland best so far. I was there for almost exactly 2 years now. I saw and experienced so much in these two years. I am very grateful for that. </p>
    <p> But everything started very turbulent. Actually, I hadn't expected a job in Ireland and looked for something else in Germany. One day a company called to me and ask if I would have time for a short conversation. It turned out that it was one of the companies that I had applied. I had completely forgotten that. 2 more days later I had the job. Over the next 4 weeks, all my friends and family helped me to dissolve my apartment in Hamburg and to clear them in a small warehouse. </p>
    <p> At that time, many of my friends asked me what you have to consider so that you can work as a German in Ireland. </p>
  </div>
</div><div class="row margin-bottom-10">
  <div class="col-md-12">
    <p> The question was answered very quickly. Just a PPS number. This is a mixture of social security and tax identification number. You can apply for this directly on site and are required for everything else such as bank account or cell phone contract. </p>
    <p> In mid -October 2010 I started in Dublin at the new company? In which all colleagues were very friendly and, above all, helpful. I quickly found new friends and felt very native to my new flat share. </p>
  </div>
