    <p> It was just stupid that I already realized on the flight to Dublin that something was not in ornament with my voice. The first few days in a foreign country and in foreign language without really talking were not easy. Especially since I had never really taken care of health/medicine in the English courses. So I am without really talking, let alone know the words to the next pharmacy and got me something to inhale by giving a few incomprehensible sounds of me and showing on my throat. It worked, the rest didn't care. </p>
    <p> Still from Germany, I organized a German -language evening in a completely unknown pub to come across like -minded people and, if necessary, get more tips. I met a really nice woman at this meeting. Your name is Sam. I have been traveling with her regularly since then and we explored a lot of angles in Ireland. Initially even smaller tours through Dublin and in the surrounding area, since my car was still in Germany at that time. Sam is still a very good friend. </p>
    <p> During this time we walked fantastic hiking trails through the city and along the coast. As soon as I brought my car to Ireland Easter 2011, travel really started. I was in Galway and on the Ring of Kerry. Visited acquaintances in Cork. I was at Giant's Causeway with Sam. We consciously dealt and landed on the beach by car. Have explored beautiful mountain landscapes. Were on the highest mountain in Wicklow. We made great rides on the beach and in the mountains. Of course, I also visited almost every major city in the two years. To name just a few: Belfast, Newcastle, Bushmills, Sligo, Donegal, Galway, Killarney, Cork, Waterford, Wexford, Kilkenny, Athlone, Wicklow and of course Dublin. </p>
