  <div class="col-md-8">
    <p> In Dublin itself I saw many beautiful and traditional pubs and of course the extraordinary pubs. I enjoyed drinks in a church converted into a pub and in an old bank building. I was seduced to the French S&eacute;ine in Irish pubs or moved back in a pub around the corner by several centuries. </p>
    <p> I was also in a wide variety of restaurants in Dublin. Starting with drunk karaoke for the evening Irish Breakfast. Burgers continued in a wide variety of restaurants to Lebanese and Tepepenyaki. </p>
    <p> I also realized with events. I was at Cirque du Soleil, Jeff Dunnham, Lord of the Rings concert, John Williams Soundtrack concert and several Klasian concerts. With the company I was in the horse and dog race. I was in the botanical garden for the orchid exhibition and visited several whiskey distilleries. Museums and galleries were of course also there. I was still at Comedy Nights and in the theater. Finally, in Dublin there were also the Tall Ships that I looked at. </p>
